<div class="about-container">
  <h1>About This Application</h1>

  <p class="intro">
    This application uses two datasets from the City of Winnipeg Open Data Portal to provide
    information about parks, districts, and park assets. The data is imported into a Rails
    database and displayed through this web application.
  </p>

  <div class="source-card">
    <h2>Parks and Open Space Data</h2>

    <p>
      This dataset contains information about parks and open spaces in Winnipeg. It provides
      details used to create park records and associate them with city districts.
    </p>

    <h3>Attributes</h3>
    <ul>
      <li>Park ID</li>
      <li>Park Name</li>
      <li>Location Description</li>
      <li>Park Category</li>
      <li>District</li>
    </ul>

    <p>
      <strong>Source:</strong><br>
      <a href="https://data.winnipeg.ca/api/v3/views/dk7c-zxyd/query.json" target="_blank">
        Parks and Open Space Data
      </a>
    </p>
  </div>

  <div class="source-card">
    <h2>Park Asset Inventory Data</h2>

    <p>
      This dataset contains information about amenities and facilities located within Winnipeg
      parks. Each asset is linked to a park using the Park ID.
    </p>

    <h3>Attributes</h3>
    <ul>
      <li>Asset ID</li>
      <li>Park ID</li>
      <li>Asset Class</li>
      <li>Asset Type</li>
      <li>Asset Size</li>
    </ul>

    <p>
      <strong>Source:</strong><br>
      <a href="https://data.winnipeg.ca/api/v3/views/tx3d-pfxq/query.json" target="_blank">
        Park Asset Inventory Data
      </a>
    </p>
  </div>
</div>